span.style: font-size: 14px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));

div.span: Every three hours, an EventBridge rule invokes a Lambda function three times with different event details.

span.style: font-size: 14px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));

div.span: The Lambda function sends 30 messages to an SQS queue with a steadily increasing delay on each message from zero seconds up to 5 minutes. The target SQS queue varies based on the event details the Lambda handler is invoked with.

span.style: font-size: 14px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));

div.span: As messages become available on the SQS queues, Lambda functions are invoked and generate hashes as a test of performance. Metrics are logged to CloudWatch Logs.

span.style: font-size: 14px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));

div.span: Using the metrics available in CloudWatch Logs, a Dashboard shows statistics based on the Lambda functions' performance.
